\pard\f0\fs28 {\b   V. pseudomirabilis} Coste,{\i  Bull. Soc. Bot. Fr.}{\b  40}: cxv (1893), from woodland on calcareous soil in S. France (Causse du Larzac, near Millau), is in some ways intermediate between {\b 12} and {\b 18}. The stems, 10-30 cm, are glabrous, the leaves shortly acuminate, the stipules ovate-lanceolate and fimbriate, the flowers large and not fragrant. The open flowers are cauline as in {\b 18}, not basal as in {\b 12}; and the fact that they are fertile and produce capsules (on long peduncles) indicates that the plants are not direct hybrids between {\b 12} and {\b 18}. W. Becker, {\i Feddes Repert. }{\b 18}:141 (1922),records {\i V.pseudomirabilis} from Bulgaria. Further investigation is needed.
