\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. V. reichenbachiana} Jordan ex Boreau,{\i  Fl. Centre Fr.} ed. 3, {\b 2}: 78 (1857) ({\i V. sylvestris} Lam. pro parte). Rosulate, with a short central shoot, a basal rosette of leaves and axillary flowering stems. Stems up to 15 cm. Leaves 2-4 cm, about as wide as long, cordate, subacute. Stipules of cauline leaves 1 cm or more, narrowly lanceolate, fimbriate; fimbriae often equalling width of stipule. Flowers 1·2-1·8 cm. Sepals acute; calycine appendages very short, inconspicuous in fruit. Petals narrow, violet, often darker at the base. Spur 3-6 mm, slender, straight, deep violet. Head of style hairy. 2n = 20.{\i  Woods and shady places. S., W. & C. Europe, extending northwards to} 60° {\i N. in Sweden and eastwards to Estonia and C. Ukraine}. Al Au Be Br Bu Co Cz Da Ga Ge Gr Hb He Ho Hs Hu It Ju Lu Po Rm Rs (B, C, W, K) Sa Si Su Tu.
